    sc "Correct."


translate English day1_fd8e485a:


    "\n Back home, the tradition is to cremate people immediately after they die. Instead of looking upon the faces of the dead, we gaze at the blazing flames that consume their bodies, enduring the distinct odor of burning flesh and saying our goodbyes to the fire."


translate English day1_1bf4cc64:


    "I was never happy with that, so one day, I asked the big man in the village about it.{w} I just realized now that he said something very similar."


translate English day1_7d3be040:


    et "Human corpses couldn't be returned to Heaven without immediately burning their bodies.{w}\nOtherwise, their lingering resentment would remain in this world, and they would become \"monsters that crawl along the ground.\""


translate English day1_654c8321:


    sc "The hunks of flesh, controlled by that sacred power, have no consciousness nor memories. They either continue moving until they run out of energy, or..."


translate English day1_c6aa3325:


    sc "...more likely, they attack people. They don't have consciousness, but still have instincts--or something like it."


translate English day1_15739252:


    sc "It's up to us to retrieve and deal with them."


